text.section:
To protect the health and safety of the public or to protect the public against misrepresentation, deceit, or fraud in the practice or teaching of barbering, the board shall promulgate administrative regulations governing the:
Location and housing of barber shops or schools;
Quantity and quality of equipment, supplies, materials, records, and furnishings required in barber shops or schools;
Qualifications of teachers of barbering;
Qualifications of applicants to or enrollees in barber schools;
Hours and courses of instruction at barber schools;
Examinations of applicants for barber or teacher of barbering; and
Qualifications of independent contract owners.
